Vietnam Airlines Corp. said nine
people were hospitalized after one of its aircraft encountered
turbulence while en route to Paris.  The Boeing Co. 777 left Hanoiâ€™s Noi Bai airport at 11:40
p.m. local time yesterday with 222 passengers and 15 crew,
state-owned Vietnam Airlines said in a statement. It arrived in
France at 7:15 a.m. local time today.  At total of 21 people were injured, with six passengers and
three flight attendants sent to hospital in Paris, the airline
said. Five of the nine have since been released.  The twin-engine 777 involved in the incident will be
examined before being returned to Hanoi, Vietnam Airlines said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
